A diamond rush in KZN’s Ladysmith has people driving in from all corners of the country following the alleged discovery of a diamond. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 LADYSMITH - The Minerals Resources Department is sending a team to Kwahlathi to investigate whether residents have discovered a massive trove of diamonds. eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli. has the details. #DStv403 #eNCA The KwaZulu-Natal government is appealing for calm after Kwahlathi residents and people from neighbouring towns flocked to the area to mine. READ: Five rare blue diamonds discovered at Cullinan mine Premier Sihle Zikalala has urged them to cease the illegal operations and allow the government team to inspect the site. Watch the video above for more details on this story.